Deadlines:
Paper Submission 1st June 2005
Notification of acceptance 15 July 2005
Camera Ready Papers 10th August 2005

Workshop 24 September 2005

Submission guidelines
Submissions  should be A4, one-column format and=20
should not exceed seven pages, including  cover=20
page,  figures, tables  and references. Times New=20
Roman 12 font is preferred. The first page should=20
state the title of the paper, the author's=20
name(s), affiliation, surface and email=20
address(es), followed by keywords and an=20
abstract. Continue with the first section of =20
your  paper.

Papers should be  submitted electronically in **PDF** format to
cri@nats.informatik.uni-hamburg.de . 

Each paper will be reviewed by up to three=20
members of the program committee. Authors of=20
accepted papers will receive guidelines regarding=20
camera-ready versions

Parallel submissions to the main conference and=20
the workshop are allowed but the review process=20
will be coordinated.  Please declare this in the=20
notification form.

